1. How would you describe your emotional state during the experience?
(1 = Very calm, 5 = Very anxious)

2. At any point, did you feel surprised or caught off guard by the events in the simulation?

3. Did you physically react to anything in the virtual experience (e.g., flinch, move, withdraw)?

4. On a scale from 1 to 5, how strongly did you feel like the virtual body or arm was your own?
(1 = Not at all, 5 = Very strongly)

5. Did the real-life physical sensations (e.g., brush or texture) affect how you experienced the simulation?
(1 = Not at all, 5 = Very much)
